Return values
Apache relies on return values from handlers to signify whether a request was handled or not, and if so, whether the
request went well or not. If a module is not interested in handling a speciﬁc request, it should always return the value
DECLINED. If it is handling a request, it should either return the generic valueOK, or a speciﬁc HTTP status code, for
