Buffering buckets
If a ﬁlter decides to store buckets beyond the duration of a single ﬁlter function invocation (for example storing them
in its ->ctx state structure), those buckets must be set aside. This is necessary because some bucket types provide
buckets which represent temporary resources (such as stack memory) which will fall out of scope as soon as the ﬁlter
chain completes processing the brigade.

